# GitNexus index scope for the Sudo_Hatter_Command home base (the LOBBY).
# Goal: graph home-base INFRA; show each project folder but NOT the files inside it.
# Paired with GITNEXUS_NO_GITIGNORE=1 at analyze time so the lobby .gitignore's
# /Projects/ rule doesn't pre-exclude the whole tree — scope lives HERE instead.
#
# Re-index after structural changes:
#   $env:GITNEXUS_NO_GITIGNORE="1"; gitnexus analyze "c:\Sudo_Hatter_Command" --index-only --name SUDO_HATTER_COMMAND -f

# --- Transient / mirror / personal — never graph these ---
_artifacts/
_my_resources/
.claude/
.opencode/
.vscode/
.gitnexus/
**/node_modules/
**/.venv/
**/__pycache__/

# --- Master toolkit (.agents/) — INTENT to graph, currently a no-op ---
# .agents/ IS the home base's primary content ("the folder is the app"), but GitNexus
# HARD-SKIPS dot-folders and .gitnexusignore negation does NOT override that (verified
# 2026-06-25 — toolkit stays out of the graph). Left as documented intent: if GitNexus
# ever exposes a "include hidden dirs" path, these take effect. Low loss for now —
# .agents/ is 1117 files but only ~10 are code; the rest are markdown with no code edges.
!.agents/
!.agents/**

# --- Projects: show the folder + its top-level marker doc(s); hide everything else. ---
# Each project surfaces as a node via its workspace map; no project source is indexed.
# (We cherry-pick which projects get FULL indexing separately, as their own repos.)
Projects/*/**
!Projects/*/AGENTS.md
!Projects/*/CLAUDE.md
!Projects/*/GEMINI.md
!Projects/*/README.md
